KgbPw9H9","label":"participant"},{"source":"recJeAtSLg0KP2loe","target":"recwmQgLTTKcYdJjk","label":"location"},{"source":"recJeAtSLg0KP2loe","target":"recthAC8bEi71Zdg1","label":"location"},{"source":"recJeAtSLg0KP2loe","target":"receEjvf5hXhkgVuZ","label":"location"},{"source":"recJeAtSLg0KP2loe","target":"recf5gqGGUdNN4pas","label":"location"},{"source":"recJeAtSLg0KP2loe","target":"recJl6YAS1kSQ6t8W","label":"predecessor"},{"source":"recJeAtSLg0KP2loe","target":"recUWXmZlrKxIx99u","label":"part of"}],"verses":[{"id":"rec9nLAJBnouNZSxT","ref":"Acts.13.4","text":"So they, being sent forth by the Holy Ghost, departed unto Seleucia; and from thence they sailed to Cyprus.","year":45},{"id":"recvo2pHYhE50X6v4","ref":"Acts.13.5","text":"And when they were at Salamis, they preached the word of God in the synagogues of the Jews: and they had also John to their minister.","year":45},{"id":"recMli10mS82DL4tc","ref":"Acts.13.6","text":"And when they had gone through the isle unto Paphos, they found a certain sorcerer, a false prophet, a Jew, whose name was Bar-jesus:","year":45},{"id":"rec29OikFdTirE0nc","ref":"Acts.13.7","text":"Which was with the deputy of the country, Sergius Paulus, a prudent man; who called for Barnabas and Saul, and desired to hear the word of God.","year":45},{"id":"recnUXfJdHA9EGTEf","ref":"Acts.13.8","text":"But Elymas the sorcerer (for so is his name by interpretation) withstood them, seeking to turn away the deputy from the faith.","year":45},{"id":"recFvvN2aXqZroCW0","ref":"Acts.13.9","text":"Then Saul, (who also is called Paul,) filled with the Holy Ghost, set his eyes on him,","year":45},{"id":"recAiqyOQr0vtDoPR","ref":"Acts.13.10","text":"And said, O full of all subtilty and all mischief, thou child of the devil, thou enemy of all righteousness, wilt thou not cease to pervert the right ways of the Lord?","year":45},{"id":"recFFtBqD7IKG8yeA","ref":"Acts.13.11","text":"And now, behold, the hand of the Lord is upon thee, and thou shalt be blind, not seeing the sun for a season. And immediately there fell on him a mist and a darkness; and he went about seeking some to lead him by the hand.","year":45}]}
